Applicability of Privacy Policy
This Privacy Policy applies to all information we collect through the Product Science Services from current and former Product Science users and visitors. This policy also covers our treatment of any personally identifiable information that our business partners share with us.
What Personal Information We Obtain and Use
Product Science uses information that you provide when you create a Product Science account, information that you upload to the Product Science Services, and information automatically collected about you when you interact with the Product Science Services.
Information You Provide to Create a Product Science Account
When you subscribe for or use the Product Science Services, or contact us for information, we collect the following personal information directly from you:  your full name, your email address, and, if applicable, the name of your company.  By voluntarily providing us with this data, you are consenting to our use of it in accordance with this Privacy Policy.
Information You Provide Additionally
If in the course of using the Product Science Services you opt to provide additional information, then this information will be used in accordance with this Privacy Policy. You may directly revise, correct, or delete the personal information you provide via your Product Science user account or by contact us at
support@productscience.ai.
Information Automatically Collected from You
In addition, the Product Science Site may also automatically receive information on our server from each user’s browser and from Product Science cookies and from third-party cookies from our web host, which is limited to essential cookies providing information on your session: user browser type, location, when you register, when you log in and when you use links to third party websites provided by the Product Science Services.  Product Science or its trusted vendors collects this data to operate effectively and provide better quality experiences.
‍
For more information about cookies, and how to disable cookies, visit http://www.allaboutcookies.org. Note that certain of the Product Science Services require certain cookies to be enabled; if all cookies are disabled, not all Services may be available to you. Certain aspects and features of the Product Science Services are only available through the use of cookies, so if you choose to disable or decline Cookies, your use of the Product Science Services may be limited or not possible.
Information We Receive from Third Parties
We do not receive personal information from third parties.
How Product Science Uses Personal Information
Product Science stores and uses personal information it collects primarily to operate effectively and provide better quality experiences, but also to:
‍
Provide, maintain and improve the Product Science Services;
Communicate with you, manage our relationship with you, which includes sending administrative information to you, such as changes to our terms, conditions, and policies, and respond to customer and prospective customer queries;
Help protect the safety of our users, which includes, without limitation, blocking suspected spammers, investigating and addressing abuse and enforcing the Product Science Terms of Service and this Privacy Policy;
Inform you of updates to the Product Science Services, security alerts and other support and administrative messages;
Communicate with you about products, services, offers and provide other news and information we think will be of interest to you (for information about how to opt out of these communications, see “Choices” below);
Monitor and analyze trends, usage and activities in connection with the Product Science Services to improve your experience and our service offerings;
Diagnose or fix technological issues; prevent fraud or criminal activities, misuse of our products or services and ensure the security of our IT systems, architecture and networks;
Comply with legal obligations and legal process;
Respond to requests from public and government authorities, including public and government authorities outside your country of residence; and
Protect our operations.
External Websites and Services
The Product Science Services may contain from time to time links to third-party websites or applications. Product Science has no control over the privacy practices or the content of any of these websites or applications. As such, we are not responsible for the practices employed by websites or services linked to or from the Product Science Services, including the information or content contained therein. Please remember that when you use a link to go from the Product Science Services to another website or applications, our Privacy Policy does not apply to third-party websites or services. You should check the applicable third-party privacy policy and terms of service when visiting any other websites or applications, and before providing any personal information to such external websites or applications. Your browsing and interaction on any third-party website or service, including those that have a link or advertisement on our website, are subject to that third party’s own rules and policies.
How We Share Personal Information
We will share the personal information that we collect and receive only with trusted third parties and business partners and only as necessary or appropriate to help us provide services to you, such as:
‍
Hosting service providers,
CRM platform integrated to collect and manage our contacts,
Our attorneys, accountants, auditors or other advisors, and
Other third-parties for any purpose with your consent or otherwise at your direction.
‍
For the hosting of and data storage for the Product Science Services, the Product Science Services and related databases are hosted on servers located in the United States. In the event of a merger, reorganization, dissolution or similar corporate event, or the sale of all or substantially all of our assets, we expect that the information that we have collected, including personal information, would be transferred to the surviving entity in a merger or the acquiring entity.  If we are involved in a merger, acquisition or asset sale, or in the unlikely event of a bankruptcy, liquidation or receivership of our business, and your personal information becomes subject to a different privacy policy, we will provide affected users notice through the Product Science Services.
Finally, we may also share such personal information where required to do so by law or subpoena or if we reasonably believe that such action is necessary to (a) comply with the law and the lawful requests by governmental, self-regulatory or other public authorities (including for the purpose of meeting national security or law enforcement requirements); (b) to enforce our terms of use or to protect the security, quality or integrity of the Product Science Services; and/or (c) to exercise or protect the rights, property, or personal safety of Product Science, our users, or others. Information shared by Product Science remains subject to this Privacy Policy.
Selling Personal Information
Product Science does not rent or sell your personal information to third parties without your consent.
Cross-Border Storage and Processing
Product Science operates from the United States of America, and the personal information we collect or receive is stored and processed in the United States of America. Product Science may transfer information that we collect about you, including personal information, to affiliated entities, or to other third parties across borders and from your country or jurisdiction to other countries or jurisdictions around the world subject to the provision of this Privacy Policy. If you are located outside of the U.S. in a jurisdiction with laws governing data collection and use that may differ from U.S. law, please note that we may maintain or transfer information, including personal information, to a country and jurisdiction that does not have the same data protection laws as your jurisdiction, and you consent to the transfer of information to the U.S. or any other country in which Product Science or its affiliates, or service providers maintain facilities and the use and disclosure of information about you as described in this Privacy Policy.
Opt-Out Choices, Notifications, and Retention of Information
Product Science provides you with the opportunity to opt out of receiving certain types of communications such as marketing communications. You may opt out of receiving promotional communications from us by following the instructions in those communications or via email at support@productscience.ai. If you do opt out, we may still send you non-promotional communications, such as information about your account or your use of the Product Science Services. By using the Product Science Services, you agree that we may communicate with you electronically.
If you deactivate your account or request that Product Science delete your personal information, we may still retain certain data and information associated with your account for record-keeping integrity, as well as to prevent fraud, collect any fees owed, enforce our terms and conditions, take actions we deem necessary to protect the integrity of our website or our users, or take other actions otherwise permitted by U.S. State and federal law.  In addition, if certain information was previously provided to third parties as described in this Privacy Policy, retention of that information will be subject to those third parties’ policies.
How We Keep Personal Information Secure
Your personal information is protected by commercial reasonable physical, electronic and procedural safeguards in compliance with applicable U.S. federal and state regulations and industry standards. We use computer safeguards such as firewalls and data encryption. In addition, we enforce physical access controls to our offices and files, and we do not authorize access to users’ personal information except for those personnel who require such access to fulfill their job responsibilities. Despite our efforts to ensure security, we cannot guarantee that personal information may not be accessed, disclosed, altered, or destroyed by a breach of our administrative, managerial and technical safeguards. Therefore, we urge you to take adequate precautions to protect your personal data as well, including, without limitation, never sharing the username and password used in connection with your participation in the Product Science Services.
Information from Minors
We do not knowingly solicit, collect or share information from any individuals under the age of 18.
Rights of California Consumers and Residents
Under California law, specific disclosures are required, and California residents have additional rights regarding their personal information. You can download a printable copy of this Privacy Policy
www.productscience.ai/privacy
.
